<paragraph blockId="48.[213,333,166,190]" box="[213,333,166,190]" pageId="48" pageNumber="1377">
<emphasis box="[213,333,166,190]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="1377">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[213,1170,206,294]" pageId="48" pageNumber="1377">
We are pleased to name this species after our good friend Roberto Caldara, who submitted to us the specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tournier" authorityYear="1878" box="[548,580,239,262]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="1377" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[548,580,239,262]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="1377">Ita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in his collection, and gave suggestions regarding the systematic position of the genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[213,382,350,374]" box="[213,382,350,374]" pageId="48" pageNumber="1377">
<emphasis box="[213,382,350,374]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="1377">Natural history</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[213,335,389,413]" box="[213,335,389,413]" pageId="48" pageNumber="1377">Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[213,311,469,493]" box="[213,311,469,493]" pageId="48" pageNumber="1377">
<emphasis box="[213,311,469,493]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="1377">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[213,1170,509,692]" pageId="48" pageNumber="1377">
The other Anatolian species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Meregalli &amp; Borovec, 2011" authorityName="Meregalli &amp; Borovec" authorityYear="2011" box="[556,698,509,533]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="1377" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="korotyaevi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[556,698,509,533]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="1377">I. korotyaevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[709,800,510,533]" pageId="48" pageNumber="1377" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, differs in the rostrum with the antennal insertion much nearer to its base, distinctly narrower at the base and nearly linearly broadened from the antennal insertion to the apex, the narrower elytral scales, particularly in their basal part, slightly raised above the integument. Also 
<taxonomicName authority="Meregalli &amp; Borovec, 2011" authorityName="Meregalli &amp; Borovec" authorityYear="2011" box="[1052,1170,606,629]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="1377" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marina" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1052,1170,606,629]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="1377">Ita marina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[213,300,637,660]" pageId="48" pageNumber="1377" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Meregalli &amp; Borovec, 2011" authorityName="Meregalli &amp; Borovec" authorityYear="2011" box="[361,492,637,661]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="1377" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="friedmani" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[361,492,637,661]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="1377">I. friedmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[502,589,637,660]" pageId="48" pageNumber="1377" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
have narrower scales, four to five times as long as wide and not completely covering the integument.
</paragraph>
